<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>28-3806</num>
  <heading>Attorney’s fees.</heading>
  <text>With respect to a consumer credit sale or direct installment loan the agreement may provide for the payment by the consumer of reasonable attorney’s fees not in excess of 15% of the unpaid balance of the obligation.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="Pub. L. 92-200" type="History">Dec. 17, 1971, 85 Stat. 670, Pub. L. 92-200, § 4</annotation>
